cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper presents a system that uses recurrent neural networks to generate angular velocities for accurate pouring of liquids. This involves robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques such as machine learning. The system also uses computer vision (cs.CV) to collect demonstrations of human pouring water. The use of neural networks and machine learning also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the system is designed for serving drinks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
